TODO List - Link External Systems
==================================

## Implemented
- [x] DataSender trait
- [x] LocalFileWriter (file-based log writer with rotation)

## Planned Senders

### ES (Elasticsearch) Sender
- [ ] Direct log shipping to Elasticsearch
- [ ] Bulk API support for batch writes
- [ ] Auto retry with exponential backoff
- [ ] FailedCache integration:
  - When ES is unavailable, cache failed logs to:
    - LocalFileWriter (file system)
    - Redis
    - Other cache backends
  - Auto replay cached logs when ES recovers

### Kafka Sender
- [ ] Async log shipping to Kafka
- [ ] Partition key support (e.g., by trace_id)

### ClickHouse Sender
- [ ] Direct insertion to ClickHouse
- [ ] Batch insert optimization

## CRD Design (EdgionLinkConfig)
```yaml
apiVersion: edgion.io/v1
kind: EdgionLinkConfig
metadata:
  name: access-log-es
spec:
  type: elasticsearch
  endpoint: https://es.example.com:9200
  auth:
    type: basic  # basic / apikey / none
    secretRef:
      name: es-credentials
  tls:
    enabled: true
    caSecretRef:
      name: es-ca-cert
  failedCache:
    type: file  # file / redis
    config:
      path: /var/log/edgion/failed-cache
      # or for redis:
      # endpoint: redis://localhost:6379
```

## Architecture
```
AccessLogger
    └── senders: Vec<Box<dyn DataSender>>
            ├── LocalFileWriter (current)
            ├── EsSender (planned)
            │       └── failedCache: Option<Box<dyn DataSender>>
            ├── KafkaSender (planned)
            └── ClickHouseSender (planned)
```
